        <h1 class="mb-3">Legislation</h1>
        <div class=" col-12">
<div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-bp-text field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p dir="rtl">.The work of the Independent Election Commission is regulated by a number of legislations&nbsp;</p>
<p dir="rtl">As an institution, <strong>The Independent Electoral Commission has constitutional status</strong> This is done through Article (2/67) of the Jordanian Constitution.</p>
<p dir="rtl">As according to<strong><a href="https://www.iec.jo/sites/default/files/2021-10/%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%88%D9%86%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87%D9%8A%D8%A6%D8%A9%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%82%D9%84%D8%A9%20%D9%84%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%A8%20%D9%88%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%87%20%D8%B1%D9%82%D9%85%2011%20%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%86%D8%A9%202012.pdf"> low </a></strong>، <strong>"Ministries, government departments, official and public institutions are obligated to provide all kinds of support and assistance requested by the authority to enable it to carry out the tasks and responsibilities assigned to it"</strong><br><br><strong>And outside the election season, </strong>The Authority is committed to its duties and role <strong><a href="https://www.iec.jo/sites/default/files/2021-10/%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%88%D9%86%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87%D9%8A%D8%A6%D8%A9%20%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%82%D9%84%D8%A9%20%D9%84%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A7%D8%A8%20%D9%88%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%87%20%D8%B1%D9%82%D9%85%2011%20%D9%84%D8%B3%D9%86%D8%A9%202012.pdf">legal </a></strong>By “Educating Voters with<strong>The importance of participation in political life </strong><u><em>including</em></u> electoral processes.</p>
<p dir="rtl">The contracts that regulate the authority's relations, starting with the constitution and ending with highly detailed reports, are regulated.</p>
